# Apex Sport Backend

## Project Structure

```
backend/
├── ApexSportApi.csproj     # Project file with dependencies
├── Program.cs              # ASP.NET Core setup & seed data
├── appsettings.json        # Configuration (DB connection string)
├── Models/
│   └── Product.cs          # Product model
├── Data/
│   └── AppDbContext.cs     # Entity Framework DbContext
├── Controllers/
│   └── ProductsController.cs # API endpoints
└── apex_sport.db           # SQLite database (auto-created)
```

## Quick Start

1. Navigate to backend:
   ```bash
   cd backend
   ```

2. Restore dependencies:
   ```bash
   dotnet restore
   ```

3. Run the server:
   ```bash
   dotnet run
   ```

Server runs on: `http://localhost:5000`

## API Endpoints

### Get All Products
```
GET /api/products
```

### Get Product by ID
```
GET /api/products/1
```

### Get Products by Category
```
GET /api/products/category/Взуття
```

## Database

- **Type:** SQLite
- **File:** `apex_sport.db` (created automatically)
- **Initial Data:** Seeded automatically on first run with sample products

## Technologies

- .NET 8.0
- ASP.NET Core
- Entity Framework Core
- SQLite
